@Chris our ALB controller is a single replica just to create ALBs that have a bunch of limitations no path routing, security groups, number of routes you can define, ...
You don't need to run skipper but we recommend to run skipper.
We run skipper as target to do the real http routing, because we know that it scales up to more than 200k routes in production. Skipper has not reload problems and no additional configuration like other ingress controllers (for example nginx). It is very flexible and can do a lot of features you might be interested if you run in production. If you are interested: <https://github.com/zalando/skipper>

