Hey, 

I'm working on having a fluentd filter to process kubernetes logs,

I edited the ConfigMap to add two files (in ingress):
      <@U1QLBGM7U> configs.d/user/filter-k8s-core-rewrite.conf
      <@U1QLBGM7U> configs.d/user/filter-k8s-core-data.conf

*First file is to rewrite the logs coming from services "origin-master" and "origin-node"*
filter-k8s-core-data.conf: |
    &lt;filter journal.system.kubernetes.master&gt;
      @type record_transformer
      enable_ruby
      &lt;record&gt;
        k8s_api ${record['MESSAGE'].match(/GET \/api/)[0]}
      &lt;/record&gt;
    &lt;/filter&gt;
*Second file is to tag all kubernetes namespaces:*
  filter-k8s-core-rewrite.conf: |
    &lt;match systemd.origin-master&gt;
      @type rewrite_tag_filter
      rewriterule1 _SYSTEMD_UNIT ^origin-master.service journal.system.kubernetes.master
      rewriterule2 _SYSTEMD_UNIT ^origin-node.service journal.system.kubernetes.node
    &lt;/match&gt;

But the problem is - what if there is no match for /.*GET/ ? What will the namespace name be?
and I'm not getting any logs under Kibana with API tags?

